# CODEOWNERS — UIx contract surface (ADR-0016 Decision 7)
#
# The `--uix-*` contract is a set of one-way doors: add a token = minor, but
# rename/remove a token, change a per-token var() fallback chain, or emit a new
# brand slot = MAJOR + an ADR (ADR-0016 Decision 2, carried from ADR-0004).
#
# With a bus-factor-1 maintainer there is no second human reviewer. CODEOWNERS is
# the automated stand-in: it forces the maintainer onto every PR that touches the
# contract so those changes are reviewed consciously, never rubber-stamped in a
# large diff. The review process for these paths is Docs/contract-change-process.md.

